---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Allergen Information" description="Important allergen and ingredient information for made-to-order cakes from GyulRose Cakes.">
  <section class="section section--blush"><div class="container prose"><p class="eyebrow">Food safety information</p><h1>Allergens and dietary requirements</h1><p class="lead">Gallery ingredient descriptions are examples from previous designs. They are not a complete allergen declaration for a future order.</p></div></section>
  <section class="section section--white"><div class="container prose"><h2>Tell us before ordering</h2><p>Use the quote form to disclose every known allergy, intolerance or dietary requirement. GyulRose must confirm the ingredients, recipe and ability to accommodate the request before the order is accepted.</p><h2>The 14 regulated allergens</h2><p>UK food businesses manage celery, cereals containing gluten, crustaceans, eggs, fish, lupin, milk, molluscs, mustard, nuts, peanuts, sesame, soya and sulphur dioxide/sulphites.</p><h2>Cross-contamination</h2><p>Do not assume that a cake is free from an allergen because that ingredient is absent from a short gallery description. Preparation environment, decorations and supplier ingredients also matter. The baker must provide the approved operational wording before this prototype is deployed.</p><h2>Information with the order</h2><p>Written allergen information should be confirmed before purchase and supplied again with collection or delivery where required. Contact GyulRose if any information is unclear before eating the cake.</p></div></section>
</BaseLayout>
